ink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqe1665702982279.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqe1665702982279.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqe1665702982279.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pqe1665702982279.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pqe1665702982279.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pqe1665702982279.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pqe1665702982279\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Screen Clearing Mnemonics\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The mnemonics for clearing all or parts of the screen only need to be defined for a display device, since printers do not have a screen to clear.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__section_x35_2c4_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d138944e51\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Mnemonics for Clearing the Screen</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Mnemonic</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Explanation</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">clear_screen</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Clear the entire screen.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Erase part of line.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code>\n</p> from (%h,%v) to (%x,%y) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Erase part of line.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code>\n</p> from (%h,%v) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqe1665702982279__table_d5609e1_d5610e1_d5611e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Erase %<var class=\"keyword varname\">m</var> or %<var class=\"keyword varname\">p</var> positions.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__section_jyy_hc4_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d138944e165\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__ul_qg1_jc4_hcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__li_d27818e1_d27819e1_d27820e1\">%<var class=\"keyword varname\">h</var>,%<var class=\"keyword varname\">v</var>—horizontal and vertical starting coordinates. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__li_d27821e1_d27822e1_d27823e1\">%<var class=\"keyword varname\">x</var>,%<var class=\"keyword varname\">y</var>—horizontal and vertical ending coordinates.\n        </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__section_rll_jc4_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d138944e192\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64016e1_d64017e1_d64018e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">clear_screen</code> mnemonic is generally\n        followed by a <code class=\"ph codeph\">cursor</code> function.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64019e1_d64020e1_d64021e1\">When interpreting <code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code>, if the\n        output sequence does not include the <var class=\"keyword varname\">%p</var>, <var class=\"keyword varname\">%x,</var> or\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">%m</var> parameters (the end position), Uniface assumes that the device is\n        not able to erase partial lines. Uniface then only uses this mnemonic if it is necessary to\n        clear an entire line. It writes spaces if a partial line erase is needed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64022e1_d64023e1_d64024e1\">The parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code> support\n        two different ways to erase a part of a line: either from a certain position (<var class=\"keyword varname\">%h,\n          %v</var>) to a certain position (<var class=\"keyword varname\">%x, %y</var>), or from a certain\n        position (<var class=\"keyword varname\">%h, %v</var>) over a certain number of positions (either\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">%m</var> or <var class=\"keyword varname\">%p</var>).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64025e1_d64026e1_d64027e1\">Uniface assumes that after <code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code>,\n        the cursor is positioned at the last cleared position. If the device does not do this, use\n        the <var class=\"keyword varname\">%p</var> parameter instead of <var class=\"keyword varname\">%m</var>. If the\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">%p</var> parameter is included in the output sequence, Uniface uses the\n        cursor position after the <code class=\"ph codeph\">erase_line</code> to reposition the cursor.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__section_hvd_mc4_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d138944e262\">Example: Examples</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64031e1_d64032e1_d64033e1\">The following example shows the definition for the\n        standard VT display:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__pre_yng_nc4_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^027[2J ^CLEAR_SCREEN\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64034e1_d64035e1_d64036e1\">The following example shows the definition for the\n        standard VT340G display:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__pre_zng_nc4_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">’S(E)T’ ^CLEAR_SCREEN\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64037e1_d64038e1_d64039e1\">The following example shows the definition for the\n        standard Sun display:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__pre_a4g_nc4_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^027[1;1H^027[J ^CLEAR_SCREEN\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64040e1_d64041e1_d64042e1\">The following example shows the definition for the\n        standard VT display:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__pre_b4g_nc4_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^027[%pX ^ERASE_LINE\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__p_d64043e1_d64044e1_d64045e1\">The following example shows the definition for the\n        standard Sun display:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pqe1665702982279__pre_c4g_nc4_hcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^027[K ^ERASE_LINE\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mzr1665702983304.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Parameters in the Output Sequence</a><p>Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531023\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Screen Clearing Mnemonics Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Screen Clearing Mnemonics The mnemonics for clearing all or parts of the screen only need to be defined for a display device, since printers do not have a screen to clear. Arguments Table 1. Mnemonics for Clearing the Screen Mnemonic Explanation clear_screen Clear the entire screen. erase_line Erase part of line. erase_line from (%h,%v) to (%x,%y) Erase part of line. erase_line from (%h,%v) Erase % m or % p positions. Parameters % h ,% v —horizontal and vertical starting coordinates. % x ,% y —horizontal and vertical ending coordinates. Description The clear_screen mnemonic is generally followed by a cursor function. When interpreting erase_line , if the output sequence does not include the %p , %x, or %m parameters (the end position), Uniface assumes that the device is not able to erase partial lines. Uniface then only uses this mnemonic if it is necessary to clear an entire line. It writes spaces if a partial line erase is needed. The parameters for erase_line support two different ways to erase a part of a line: either from a certain position ( %h, %v ) to a certain position ( %x, %y ), or from a certain position ( %h, %v ) over a certain number of positions (either %m or %p ). Uniface assumes that after erase_line , the cursor is positioned at the last cleared position. If the device does not do this, use the %p parameter instead of %m . If the %p parameter is included in the output sequence, Uniface uses the cursor position after the erase_line to reposition the cursor. Example: Examples The following example shows the definition for the standard VT display: ^027[2J ^CLEAR_SCREEN Copy The following example shows the definition for the standard VT340G display: ’S(E)T’ ^CLEAR_SCREEN Copy The following example shows the definition for the standard Sun display: ^027[1;1H^027[J ^CLEAR_SCREEN Copy The following example shows the definition for the standard VT display: ^027[%pX ^ERASE_LINE Copy The following example shows the definition for the standard Sun display: ^027[K ^ERASE_LINE Copy Related Links Parameters in the Output Sequence Some mnemonics include parameters in the output sequence that can be used to determine layout and formatting information, such as horizontal and vertical coordinates, numeric base zero (decimal, octal, or hexadecimal), zero padding, and so on. The output sequence can even include expressions that use the parameters incalculation, for example, to increment values. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}